






@(1-3=c3119.1) Say to @wRN{Ibbi-@wDN{Suen}}, my lord: this is what @wPN{Puzur-@wRN{Šulgi}}, the governor of @wSN{Kazallu}, your servant, says:

@(4-6=c3119.4) A messenger of @wRN{Išbi-@wDN{Erra}} came to me. He presented himself before me announcing: @q[messenger,Puzur-Culgi]{“@wRN{Išbi-@wDN{Erra}}, my lord, sends you a message:”

@(7-14=c3119.7) @q[,]{“@q[Icbi-Erra,messenger]{“@wDN{Enlil}, my lord, has …… the shepherdship of the land. @wDN{Enlil} has told me to bring before @wDN{Ninisina} the cities, deities and troops of the region of the @wWN{Tigris}, @wWN{Euphrates}, @wWN{Ab-gal} and @wWN{Me-@wDN{Enlila}} watercourses, from the province of @wGN{Ḫamazi} 
{to the sea of @wGN{Magan}
} 
{@noteanchor{1 ms. has instead:} and from the …… of @wGN{Magan}
} , so as to make @wSN{Isin} the storehouse of @wDN{Enlil}, to make it famous, and 
{to make those regions its spoils of war and to make @wSN{Isin's} citizens occupy their cities
} 
{@noteanchor{1 ms. has instead:} to make @wSN{Isin's} citizens occupy the cities as spoils of war.
} ””


@(15-17=c3119.15) @q[,]{“@q[,]{“Why do you oppose (?) me? 
{I swear by the name of my lord @wDN{Enlil} and by @wDN{Dagan}, my personal god
} 
{@noteanchor{2 mss. have instead:} I swear by the name of @wDN{Dagan}, my personal god
} , that I will indeed get hold of @wSN{Kazallu}!””


